The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Aloke confident of chances 

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: The 20-member Bengal squad for the 60th Santosh Trophy was announced on Sunday. Coach Aloke Mukherjee said: I am happy with the squad and the boys are in good shape. I am planning to play in 4-4-2 format. 

Bengal are in cluster VIII with Mizoram, Nagaland and AP. Mukherjee is not willing to take chances. You cant take any of the teams lightly, because upsets can happen. We have to play to our full potential. 

The SQUAD: Goalkeepers: Rajat Ghosh Dastidar, Kalyan Chowbey, Subrata Pal; Defenders: Shankar Roy Choudhuri, Madhab Das, Saumik Dey, Shubash Chakraborty, Covan Lawrence, Amulya Mondal, Manas Das, Rajiv Ahmed; Midfielders: Chandan Das (vice-captain), Mehtab Hossain, Shashti Duley, Noel Wilson, Jayanta Sen; Forwards: Bhaichung Bhutia (captain), Rahim Nabi, Raman Vijayan, Dipendu Biswas. Coach: Aloke Mukherjee. 




